      "body" : "@laanwj I wrote the following script ...\r\n\r\n```bash\r\n#!/bin/bash\r\n\r\nfor H in $(git grep \"\" -- \"*.h\" | cut -f1 -d: | uniq); do\r\n    CPP=${H/%\\.h/.cpp}\r\n    if [[ ! -e $CPP ]]; then\r\n        continue\r\n    fi\r\n    cat \"$H\" \"$CPP\" | grep -E \"^#include \" | sort | uniq -c | \\\r\n      grep \" 2 #include\" && echo \"$CPP\" && echo\r\ndone\r\n```\r\n\r\n... to identify `.cpp` files that re-include the includes already included in its corresponding `.h` file. See PR #10574.",
